 {"id":"flywheel_gateway-brp","title":"Integrate AI hints into all error responses","description":"# Task: Integrate AI Hints into All Error Responses

## Parent Epic
[Epic] AI Hints in Error Responses (flywheel_gateway-1n6)

## Objective
Modify all error handling code to include AI hints (severity, suggestedAction, alternativeApproach) from the existing ai-hints.ts file.

## Current State
AI hints exist in `packages/shared/src/errors/ai-hints.ts`:
```typescript
AGENT_NOT_FOUND: {
  severity: "terminal",
  suggestedAction: "List active agents and use a valid agent ID.",
  alternativeApproach: "Spawn a new agent if the intended one was terminated.",
}
```

But error responses don't include them:
```json
{ "error": { "code": "AGENT_NOT_FOUND", "message": "Agent not found" } }
```

## Target State
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "AGENT_NOT_FOUND",
    "message": "Agent not found",
    "severity": "terminal",
    "hint": "List active agents and use a valid agent ID.",
    "alternative": "Spawn a new agent if the intended one was terminated."
  }
}
```

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Update wrapError utility
Already planned in response wrapper task, but ensure it:
- Looks up AI hints by error code
- Includes severity, hint, alternative fields

### 2. Update route error handlers
Each route's handleError function needs to use wrapError:
- `agents.ts`: handleAgentError
- `reservations.ts`: handleError
- `conflicts.ts`: (inline error handling)
- `checkpoints.ts`: handleError
- `dcg.ts`: handleError
- `mail.ts`: handleError, respondWithGatewayError
- `utilities.ts`: handleError
- `beads.ts`: (check implementation)
- `alerts.ts`: (check implementation)

### 3. Update WebSocket error messages
`ws/handlers.ts` error responses should also include hints:
```typescript
const errorMsg: ServerMessage = {
  type: "error",
  code: "FORBIDDEN",
  message: `Subscription denied: ${authResult.reason}`,
  severity: "terminal",
  hint: AI_HINTS.WS_SUBSCRIPTION_DENIED.suggestedAction,
};
```

### 4. Ensure all error codes have hints
Review `ai-hints.ts` to ensure coverage for:
- All codes in `error-codes.ts`
- WebSocket-specific error codes
- Validation error codes

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] wrapError includes hints for known error codes
- [ ] All route error handlers use wrapError
- [ ] WebSocket errors include hints
- [ ] All error codes have corresponding hints
- [ ] Tests verify hints are included
- [ ] Documentation updated

## Testing
```typescript
describe("error responses", () => {
  it("includes AI hints for known error codes", async () => {
    const res = await app.request("/agents/nonexistent");
    const body = await res.json();

    expect(body.error.severity).toBe("terminal");
    expect(body.error.hint).toContain("List active agents");
  });

  it("works without hints for unknown codes", async () => {
    // Custom error code should still work
    const res = await triggerUnknownError();
    const body = await res.json();

    expect(body.error.code).toBeDefined();
    expect(body.error.severity).toBeUndefined(); // OK, not required
  });
});
```

## Dependencies
- Depends on: Create response wrapper utility functions (flywheel_gateway-3ib)
- Depends on: Define canonical response envelope types (flywheel_gateway-amj)

## Files to Modify
- `packages/shared/src/api/response-utils.ts`
- `packages/shared/src/errors/ai-hints.ts` (add missing hints)
